  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nIt would be great if we have an extension of ERC721 that allows non collateralized lending / borrowing of NFT. It has so many use cases.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nA user can lend his/her NFT to another user for some period of time after that time the NFT goes back to the actual owner, during the borrow period the owner of the NFT is the borrower, but the borrower cannot transfer the NFT to some other accout. I have written the code please check and share your opinions.\r\nhttps://github.com/Ijlal-Ishaq/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC721/extensions/ERC721Borrowable.sol\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- Make sure that you have reviewed the OpenZeppelin Contracts Contributor Guidelines. -->\r\n<!-- https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md -->\r\n",
